article.description: Texas St. beats Arkansas-Little Rock 77-74 in 2OT
article.headline: Texas St. beats Arkansas-Little Rock 77-74 in 2OT
article.linkText: Texas St. beats Arkansas-Little Rock 77-74 in 2OT
article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas -- D.J. Brown scored 16 points, including the winning 3-pointer in double overtime, to lead Texas State past Arkansas-Little Rock 77-74 on Thursday night. A three-point play by Kavin Gilder-Tilbury gave Texas State (9-4, 3-1 Sun Belt) a 74-69 lead with 2:07 left. A jumper by Ben Dillard and a 3 by Josh Hagins with 6 seconds left tied it at 74, setting up Brown's heroics. Hagins, who led UALR (5-9, 0-4) with 18 points, made a layup with 1:28 left in the first overtime which gave the Trojans a 65-61 lead, but Gilder Tilbury -- who scored 10 of his 15 points after the end of regulation -- hit 4 of 4 free throws to force the second overtime. UALR's Roger Woods made a layup with 3 seconds left in regulation to tie it at 56. Ethan Montalvo had 15 points and Emani Gant added 13 and eight rebounds for Texas State.
